0 full-color images and more than 40 case studies that profile key species worldwide. Each chapter covers a different type of nest, from tunnel nests and mound nests to floating nests, hanging nests, woven nests, and even multiple-nest avian cities. Other kinds of avian construction—such as bowers and food stores—are also featured.Now with more case studies and an updated foreword, this revised and expanded edition includes intricate step-by-step sequences, visual spreads on nest-building materials and methods, and insightful commentary by a leading expert.Illustrates how birds around the world design, engineer, and build their nestsFeatures architectural blueprints, step-by-step sequences, visual spreads on nest-building materials and methods, and expert commentaryIncludes more than 300 full-color imagesCovers more than 100 bird species worldwide  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBirdsxBehavior. 0aBirdsxNestsvPictorial works. 0aBirdsxNests. 0aNest building. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Zoology / Ornithology.2bisacsh1 aWilliams, Tony D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Tony D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074975540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691256252?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691256252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691256252/original  a978-3-11-074975-5  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles